.TH "itcw_set_data" 9 "itcw_set_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
itcw_set_data \- set data address and tida flag of the itcw
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" itcw_set_data
.BI "(struct itcw *itcw "  ","
.BI "void *addr "  ","
.BI "int use_tidal "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "itcw" 12
address of the itcw
.IP "addr" 12
the data address
.IP "use_tidal" 12
zero of the data address specifies a contiguous block of data,
non-zero if it specifies a list if tidaws.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the input/output data address of the itcw (depending on the value of the
r-flag and w-flag). If \fIuse_tidal\fP is non-zero, the corresponding tida flag
is set as well.
